 A lot of the stories in the Bible are actually God's story.

266
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:23,360
 What is God doing in this man's life?

267
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:29,360
 And that story tells of his character, God's own character,

268
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:31,880
 who God really is.

269
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:34,720
 So here, I have two main points.

270
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:37,600
 One, as we dig deeper into the story,

271
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:42,600
 we find that the divine providence triumphs over even evil.

272
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:46,160
 And second point is providence moves in silence.

273
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:50,160
 First point, perhaps you need to understand this story

274
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:54,600
 is to understand the overall flow of the chapter.

275
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:58,160
 Now, this chapter has three paragraphs.

276
00:13:58,160 --> 00:14:01,760
 Outline the passage, you find there were three paragraphs,

277
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:06,760
 1 to 6a, 6b to 19, and 20 to 23.

278
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:12,640
 It's funny, interesting, in the first part of the story,

279
00:14:12,640 --> 00:14:17,080
 1 to 6a, Joseph was in poverty's house,

280
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:19,880
 but there's a phrase that is repeated.

281
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:24,080
 The Lord was with Joseph, Yahweh was with him,

282
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:25,600
 and giving him success.

283
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:31,480
 And then the second part of the story, 6b to 19,

284
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:33,880
 you find that this phrase is absent.

285
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:39,680
 There's no obvious presence of God,

286
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:44,640
 even when Joseph was in trouble, right?

287
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:49,640
 In fact, the cloak, the clothe that Joseph was wearing

288
00:14:49,640 --> 00:14:54,080
 that Joseph is wearing, remember the story of Joseph

289
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:57,480
 has to do with what he wears all the time, right?

290
00:14:57,480 --> 00:15:00,920
 Chapter 37, he got the many colored cloth

291
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:03,960
 from his loving father, right?

292
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:06,600
 And then chapter 39 right here,

293
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:11,600
 his clothes is in the hand of Paul's wife.

294
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:19,960
 Now the word hand can mean power and authority.

295
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:21,680
 So in the middle part of the story,

296
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:26,360
 Joseph, unfortunately, is under P.W.'s hands,

297
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,880
 Paul's wife, okay?

298
00:15:27,880 --> 00:15:30,480
 Paul's wife, P.W.

299
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:36,720
 Seizes the clothe and kept it under her guard

300
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:39,040
 to accuse him, right?

301
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:42,880
 She screamed and he went outside

302
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:45,440
 and leaving the clothe with P.W.

303
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:48,960
 And in this story, Joseph is under the hand

304
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:51,840
 and the power of P.W.

305
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:53,480
 Where's God?

306
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:55,240
 God is not there.

307
00:15:55,240 --> 00:15:59,080
 At least it's not explicitly mentioned.

308
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:03,840
 And then you go to the third part, 20 to 23.

309
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:08,560
 Joseph is in the prison, the royal prison,

310
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:10,920
 but then the phrase shows up again.

311
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:15,920
 The Lord was with Joseph, giving him success.

312
00:16:15,920 --> 00:16:18,560
 Now, when we talk about divine providence,

313
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:21,760
 we have to deal with the inevitable tension

314
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:26,160
 between God's sovereignty, God's control in your life,

315
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:28,080
 and also human suffering.

316
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:31,160
 Now, a lot of people do not believe in the Bible

317
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:34,520
 or resist the idea of the existence of God

318
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:38,040
 because they have seen so much suffering in the world.

319
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:41,320
 There are so many troubles in the world, right?

320
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:42,960
 You read the recent news,

321
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:45,160
 what happened in Israel, Gaza.

322
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:49,120
 Hundreds of people died, innocent people.

323
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:51,120
 And to a lot of people, this is enough

324
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:57,160
 for them to say, "God, if you exist,

325
00:16:57,160 --> 00:16:59,000
 "why all the troubles, right?

326
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,200
 "Why all the suffering?"

327
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:04,000
 Now, this story tells us, or trying to

328
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:08,680
 sort out the tension between God's sovereignty

329
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:11,280
 and human suffering.

330
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:12,600
 Now, the Bible never said,

331
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:18,480
 the Bible never says that God caused PW to tempt Joseph.

332
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:22,840
 The Bible is clear on this.

333
00:17:22,840 --> 00:17:26,080
 Although the Bible, there's no anti-philosophical answer

334
00:17:26,080 --> 00:17:28,120
 to the problem of evil.

335
00:17:28,120 --> 00:17:31,440
 In fact, there's none, right?

336
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:36,000
 If you read all the works of all the great philosophers

337
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:39,080
 who are trying to figure out or sort out

338
00:17:39,080 --> 00:17:41,920
 the sovereignty of God and human suffering,

339
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:46,080
 there's no airtight philosophical rational answer

340
00:17:46,080 --> 00:17:47,280
 to explain the two.

341
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:49,720
 Never.

342
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:54,240
 Even, you get that, even you have a rational understanding

343
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:59,240
 or comprehensive answer to why suffering happened to me,

344
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:02,320
 why suffering happened to other people,

345
00:18:02,320 --> 00:18:06,600
 even you get the answer, the Bible says, "So what?"

346
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:10,040
 Because you are still experiencing suffering, right?

347
00:18:10,040 --> 00:18:11,240
 You still see suffering.

348
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:14,000
 In fact, we don't need one.

349
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,360
 The Bible is clear.

350
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:21,200
 The Bible uses stories to try to explain that.

351
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:24,360
 And as we all know, human language has its limit.

352
00:18:24,360 --> 00:18:28,640
 And when you hit that limit, storytelling comes.

353
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:30,680
 Because story has the power to explain,

354
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:34,520
 more so than statements that we make.

355
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:36,560
 So the language is important.

356
00:18:36,560 --> 00:18:41,560
 The Bible is clear that God does not cause suffering

357
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:42,760
 to happen.

358
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:46,520
 Perhaps there's no better term.

359
00:18:46,520 --> 00:18:51,520
 We should say God allows or God tolerates evil

360
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:53,800
 or suffering to come to pass.

361
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:58,800
 At best, we must say God permits or allows

362
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:01,840
 some bad things happen to us.

363
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:07,960
 Joseph begins with a position of honor,

364
00:19:07,960 --> 00:19:10,040
 being loved by his loving father.

365
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:13,720
 And now he come to the bottom of the valley.

366
00:19:13,720 --> 00:19:17,880
 That's a story trying to tell us.

367
00:19:17,880 --> 00:19:22,520
 But he is here in the position of shame at the end of chapter

368
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:25,160
 or in the middle part of the chapter,

369
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:29,600
 is to prepare him for the next thing to happen.

370
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:34,600
 God's providence is still there when he faces difficulties,

371
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:39,320
 temptations, and challenges.

372
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:43,880
 Indeed, the power of God triumphs over all of this evil

373
00:19:43,880 --> 00:19:45,640
 things in his life.

374
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:51,280
 So that's how the story goes, showing you who God is.

375
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:54,800
 He can triumph over all the troubles.

376
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:56,880
 And that is true for Joseph.

377
00:19:56,880 --> 00:20:00,120
 That is true for you and true for me.

378
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:03,960
 For a little while, Joseph suffered.

379
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:05,800
 He did, he suffered.

380
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:10,200
 But at the end of the episode, God raised him up again.

381
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:13,080
 That is what God is doing in the life of Joseph.

382
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:18,040
 And that should be also the case for all of you,

383
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:19,400
 for all of us.

384
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:23,240
 So God triumphs over evil and suffering.

385
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:26,760
 But you take deeper into the story,

386
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:30,840
 the providence of God actually moves in silence.

387
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:36,000
 You have to pay attention, look closely to this chapter.

388
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,360
 And if you divide this chapter as I did

389
00:20:38,360 --> 00:20:40,840
 into three different paragraphs,

390
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:45,400
 you can also subtitle each part as so.

391
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:48,920
 The first part, Joseph in providence's house,

392
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:52,840
 God is there, clearly, explicitly stated.

393
00:20:52,840 --> 00:20:56,720
 6B to 19, in the hand of P.W.,

394
00:20:56,720 --> 00:20:59,880
 God seems to be silent.

395
00:20:59,880 --> 00:21:02,640
 God seems to be absent.

396
00:21:02,640 --> 00:21:07,520
 20 to 23, again, God is there.

397
00:21:07,520 --> 00:21:11,520
 You see, in this chapter of Joseph's life,

398
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:15,080
 God is there in the beginning, in Egypt.

399
00:21:15,960 --> 00:21:20,960
 And sandwiched between it is God seems to be silent

400
00:21:20,960 --> 00:21:23,640
 in times of difficulties.

401
00:21:23,640 --> 00:21:26,560
 Is God really absent?

402
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:29,880
 That's the question the chapter's trying to pose to us

403
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:31,200
 as readers.

404
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:36,200
 Is Joseph merely under the mercy of P.W.?

405
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:39,200
 Is he really?

406
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:40,880
 Or is not?

407
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:45,640
 As I try to understand this providence,

408
00:21:45,640 --> 00:21:47,640
 this teaching of providence,

409
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:49,640
 trying to understand what God is doing

410
00:21:49,640 --> 00:21:52,800
 in this episode of Joseph's life,

411
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:57,120
 I must admit at first, I don't quite understand.

412
00:21:57,120 --> 00:22:00,720
 But then I noticed some of the details

413
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:02,000
 that I didn't see before.

414
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:05,200
 Okay, this is what I noticed.

415
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:09,760
 I noticed a subtle changes,

416
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:13,440
 subtle progression of where Joseph is.

417
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:19,760
 He started off in poverty's house in Egypt.

418
00:22:19,760 --> 00:22:22,360
 Then bad things happened to him.

419
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:27,560
 And then the location changes to the prison.

420
00:22:27,560 --> 00:22:31,000
 That is so bad, right?

421
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:35,120
 However, the word king shows up the first time

422
00:22:35,120 --> 00:22:36,800
 in Joseph's story.

423
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:40,280
 He end up in the prison of the royal house, yes, indeed.

424
00:22:40,320 --> 00:22:45,320
 However, it is the prison of the kings, the pharaoh.

425
00:22:45,320 --> 00:22:51,320
 Now, why is this location change significant?

426
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:55,240
 As we all know, the whole story of Joseph,

427
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:59,320
 we know Joseph is moving closer and closer and closer,

428
00:22:59,320 --> 00:23:04,320
 one step at a time to the royal court of the king of Egypt.

429
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:07,320
 And God is preparing him,

430
00:23:07,320 --> 00:23:12,000
 even in the midst of misfortunes happen along the way.

431
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:15,760
 God allows or tolerates something bad happened to Joseph,

432
00:23:15,760 --> 00:23:20,760
 but he is slowly, gradually moving Joseph closer

433
00:23:20,760 --> 00:23:23,880
 and closer to the king of Egypt, to pharaoh.

434
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:26,760
 At the end, as we know,

435
00:23:26,760 --> 00:23:31,760
 Joseph was being placed there in the courthouse of pharaoh

436
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:37,640
 in order to save the whole family of Israel

437
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:41,520
 and indeed plus many other people who suffer from famine.

438
00:23:41,520 --> 00:23:44,000
 So God has a bigger plan, right?

439
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:49,040
 God can use evil and indeed triumphs over evil

440
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:51,600
 to accomplish his will.

441
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:55,040
 God seems to be absent,

442
00:23:55,040 --> 00:23:59,240
 but that does not mean God is not working behind the scene.

443
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:00,080
 Right?

444
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:03,080
 As you observe your life,

445
00:24:03,080 --> 00:24:08,440
 as you think about the journey of your life,

446
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:09,720
 all the twists and turns,

447
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:14,640
 if you think about it in light of God's presence,

448
00:24:14,640 --> 00:24:20,200
 what a huge difference the people that you have met,

449
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:26,360
 the accidents that happen in our lives,

450
00:24:26,360 --> 00:24:28,640
 but in God's sight, there's no accident.

451
00:24:28,640 --> 00:24:30,920
 It's just incident.

452
00:24:31,920 --> 00:24:33,520
 What is God doing in your life?

453
00:24:33,520 --> 00:24:40,040
 Why is God silent or seemingly silent, seemingly absent,

454
00:24:40,040 --> 00:24:45,120
 especially in times of difficulty, times of uncertainty?

455
00:24:45,120 --> 00:24:48,920
 In the past few months, I've been struggling with

456
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:52,880
 just so much struggle in the presence of God.

457
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:58,360
 I prayed for something and it didn't happen.

458
00:24:58,360 --> 00:25:00,720
 And there was a spiritual battle inside of me.

459
00:25:01,120 --> 00:25:02,280
 God, what are you doing?

460
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:03,880
 What the heck are you doing, God?

461
00:25:03,880 --> 00:25:05,120
 Right?

462
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:08,200
 And there was so many sleepless night

463
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:13,200
 and I struggled with my prayers, my wish, my desire,

464
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:16,400
 not happening according to my will.

465
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:20,560
 And then it turned out, praise God, right?

466
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:22,160
 It did happen.

467
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:25,400
 And of course, according to God's good will.

468
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:29,560
 Philip Yancy, ring any bell?

469
00:25:29,560 --> 00:25:32,680
 Christian thinker, Christian writer.

470
00:25:32,680 --> 00:25:36,040
 He has written many, many books about sufferings,

471
00:25:36,040 --> 00:25:39,280
 many, many books about divine providence.

472
00:25:39,280 --> 00:25:43,520
 And in one of his stories,

473
00:25:43,520 --> 00:25:48,760
 Yancy talks about his struggle with divine silence,

474
00:25:48,760 --> 00:25:52,240
 that God doesn't seem to be working.

475
00:25:52,240 --> 00:25:55,840
 God doesn't seem to be moving.

476
00:25:55,840 --> 00:25:59,880
 When he pray so hard, diligently every single day,

477
00:25:59,880 --> 00:26:04,000
 he feels like God is ignoring his prayers,

478
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,240
 denying his request.

479
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:11,240
 And one of those moments, he wanted to give up, right?

480
00:26:11,240 --> 00:26:15,040
 And then he thought of something in the Bible.

481
00:26:15,040 --> 00:26:19,720
 And that something in the Bible, he thought of,

482
00:26:19,720 --> 00:26:23,760
 was Jesus in Gethsemane.

483
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:28,760
 Remember the last night of the life of Jesus,

484
00:26:28,760 --> 00:26:31,520
 he was in the garden, he was praying so hard.

485
00:26:31,520 --> 00:26:33,320
 He prayed that the Father would take away

486
00:26:33,320 --> 00:26:36,840
 the cup of suffering, death on the cross,

487
00:26:36,840 --> 00:26:38,480
 soon to happen from him.

488
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:42,920
 He was praying so hard in the garden in Gethsemane,

489
00:26:42,920 --> 00:26:45,360
 that prayed that God would remove that cup.

490
00:26:45,360 --> 00:26:49,400
 And God denied his prayer.

491
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:54,200
 It is so-called the first prayer in Jesus' life,

492
00:26:54,200 --> 00:26:56,680
 or the only prayer in Jesus' life,

493
00:26:56,680 --> 00:26:59,600
 that God did not answer the way his son prayed.

494
00:26:59,600 --> 00:27:02,680
 His son prayed, finally,

495
00:27:02,680 --> 00:27:06,600
 "Not according to my will, but your will."

496
00:27:06,600 --> 00:27:09,920
 So Yancy wrote this paragraph.

497
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:14,400
 He said, "How many times have I prayed for one thing,

498
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:16,720
 "only to receive another?

499
00:27:16,720 --> 00:27:19,500
 "God alone is qualified to answer prayer.

500
00:27:19,500 --> 00:27:23,560
 "And there's some time we have to let go and trust God.

501
00:27:23,560 --> 00:27:26,920
 "Who can transmute our self-focused request

502
00:27:26,920 --> 00:27:30,240
 "into an unimaginably larger plan?

503
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:36,200
 "When Jesus prayed to the one who could save him from death,

504
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:39,200
 "Jesus did not get that salvation.

505
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:44,120
 "Indeed, Jesus got the salvation of the whole world."

506
00:27:44,120 --> 00:27:47,240
 That is amazing.

507
00:27:47,240 --> 00:27:51,660
 God did not answer his son's prayer the way he wanted.

508
00:27:52,800 --> 00:27:56,340
 But God has a bigger, bigger, larger plan.

509
00:27:56,340 --> 00:27:59,640
 Yet Jesus was not saved from death.

510
00:27:59,640 --> 00:28:06,360
 But in Jesus' death, he saved many others in the world.

511
00:28:06,360 --> 00:28:09,760
 That is the divine providence of God.

512
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:12,380
 Look at our lives, right?

513
00:28:12,380 --> 00:28:14,400
 There are many requests, there are many prayers

514
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:19,200
 maybe delayed, or even God said explicitly, "No."

515
00:28:20,800 --> 00:28:24,680
 But we have to remember, who got the bigger plan in mind?

516
00:28:24,680 --> 00:28:27,780
 Not us, right?

517
00:28:27,780 --> 00:28:31,000
 We can only see a few steps ahead of us,

518
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:32,700
 but God sees everything.

519
00:28:32,700 --> 00:28:37,280
 Let me end with the Confession of Faith of Westminster.

520
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:40,080
 Again, this document, a theological document,

521
00:28:40,080 --> 00:28:46,160
 written in 1646, 17th century.

522
00:28:46,560 --> 00:28:50,880
 But it has been one of the best treatment

523
00:28:50,880 --> 00:28:53,800
 of all the doctrines in summarizing

524
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:56,320
 all the important teachings of the Bible.

525
00:28:56,320 --> 00:29:01,320
 In chapter three, article three, five, article three,

526
00:29:01,320 --> 00:29:04,720
 it says, "God uses ordinary means

527
00:29:04,720 --> 00:29:07,780
 "to work out his providence day by day.

528
00:29:07,780 --> 00:29:12,220
 "But as God pleases, God may work without,

529
00:29:13,040 --> 00:29:17,740
 "beyond, or contrary to those human means."

