 perhaps the most devilish means, the crucifixion.

543
00:30:11,040 --> 00:30:16,040
 His son died unjustly on the cross.

544
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:20,160
 But God triumphs over all and accomplishes his will,

545
00:30:20,160 --> 00:30:24,460
 his holy purpose for saving us sinners from sin, from death.

546
00:30:24,460 --> 00:30:30,480
 There are moments in our lives, God may be silent.

547
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:34,920
 He may be quiet, but God is not absent.

548
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:38,400
 There are moments in our lives,

549
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:42,080
 we may experience God as if he's a passive God,

550
00:30:42,080 --> 00:30:43,280
 detached from us.

551
00:30:43,280 --> 00:30:46,920
 But the story tells us who God really is.

552
00:30:46,920 --> 00:30:52,280
 He's still working, still working behind the scene.

553
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:55,000
 Look at the cross, look at the crucifixion

554
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:56,860
 of his own one and only son.

555
00:30:56,860 --> 00:30:58,920
 He's still there.

556
00:30:58,920 --> 00:31:02,520
 He's still there in the life of Joseph.

557
00:31:02,520 --> 00:31:04,000
 He's still there in your life.

558
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:06,040
 Let's all pray together.

